QRCODE
structure:
    A, The Data(bit string):

        Prerequisites: 
        -Determine the smallest version possible: https://www.thonky.com/qr-code-tutorial/character-capacities

        -Find the maximum bit length according to EC level and version: https://www.thonky.com/qr-code-tutorial/error-correction-table

        1, Mode: Numeric 0001, Alphanum 0010, Byte 0100, Kanji 1000, ECI 0111

        2, Character count: The character count in binary, the length in bits is dependent on mode and version: (https://www.thonky.com/qr-code-tutorial/data-encoding#step-1-choose-the-error-correction-level)

        3, Encoded Data, in binary
        
        4, Terminator: string of at most four 0s, less if that number is needed to reach the limit bit count
        
        5, If bit count is not a multiplication of 8, add 0s until it is
        
        6, If the bit string is not maximum capacity, add "11101100 00010001"s until it is
    B, The ECC:

        Prerequisites: Find the amount of ECC codewords (string of 8-bit) to be used: https://www.thonky.com/qr-code-tutorial/error-correction-table
